icontrol.drivers.instruments.hp

Class HP4192

  • java.lang.Object
    • icontrol.drivers.Device
      • icontrol.drivers.instruments.hp.HP4192

  • @iC_Annotation(CommPorts=GPIB,
               InstrumentClassName="HP 4192")
public class HP4192
extends Device
    Hewlett-Packard 4192A LF Impedance Analyzer.

    All device commands that the Hewlett-Packard 4192A understands are implemented here.

    The main body of this class was copied to AgilentE4980A, so if this class is modified, it might be a good idea to modify AgilentE4980A as well.

    Instrument Commands:

    • Init(int, boolean, int)
    • SweepFthenV(double, double, double, boolean, double, double, double, boolean, int, String)
    • Trigger()
    • setAC_Amplitude(double)
    • setSpotBias(double)
    • setSpotFrequency(double)
    Version:
    0.4
    Author:
    KPP (Kurt Pernstich: pernstich@alumni.ethz.ch)

      • Open

        public void Open()
          throws java.io.IOException
        Override the default Open method in the Device class because this Instrument does not support IEEE 488.2 calls which are used in the default implementation.

        It is convenient to clear the queue here.

        Overrides:
        Open in class Device
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if the queue could not be cleared; bubbles up from ClearQueue.

      • ClearQueue

        private void ClearQueue()
                 throws java.io.IOException
        Checks if the Instrument requests service, and if it does, the Instrument is addressed to talk so that the unfetched data is read to empty the output buffer of the 4192 and end the service request.

        NOTE: Receiving the Status Byte is only implemented when using driver classes derived from GPIB_Driver and an Exception is thrown if some other driver is used (at the time of writing, no such driver exists).

        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - When GPIB communication caused an error; bubbles up from QueryInstrument.

      • Measure

        private HP4192.MValue Measure()
                       throws java.io.IOException,
                              javax.script.ScriptException
        Triggers a measurement and reads the Instrument's response. The method returns with the default values for ret (Z and phi are NaN) if the received answer was not as expected. The returned value is always an impedance value (Z) even if the circuit mode was parallel.
        Returns:
        Returns an MValue object with the measured Z and phi values or NaN if the measurement was invalid> The returned value always contains an impedance value (Z) even if the circuit mode is parallel (Y is converted to Z in this case).
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - re-thrown from SendToInstrument
        javax.script.ScriptException - re-thrown from Utilities.getFloat

                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                throws javax.script.ScriptException,
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       java.io.IOException,
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       java.util.zip.DataFormatException
        Sweeps the frequency for all given DC biases and stores the impedance.
        Parameters:
        FreqStart - Start Frequency
        FreqStop - Stop Frequency
        FreqInc - Increment in Frequency respectively number of points per decade. See Utilities.GenerateValues
        FreqLog - When false the frequency points are equally spaced; if true they are logarithmically spaced. See GenerateValues
        VStart - First DC bias
        VStop - Last DC bias
        VInc - Increment in the DC bias respectively number of points per decade (see GenerateValues).
        VLog - When false the voltage points are equally spaced; if true they are logarithmically spaced. See GenerateValues
        VDelay - Time delay after applying the dC bias and starting the frequency sweep.
        FileExtension - This String is appended to the File Name. If the filename already exists, a new file with a counter is inserted between the FileName and the FileExtension.
        Throws:
        javax.script.ScriptException - When generating the voltage or frequency values failed (bubbles up from GenerateValues).
        java.io.IOException - When communication with the Instrument failed (bubbled up from setSpotBias or setSpotFrequency.
        java.util.zip.DataFormatException - when the Syntax Check failed.
